The turning of the seasons<br>
A time where your spirit will be set free<br>
And people will wander, for their own reasons<br>
<br>
To find what is missing<br>
What is not in their life<br>
Whether it's a few hugs or some kissing<br>
A lover, or a wife<br>
<br>
But all some people ever look for<br>
And all some people ever need<br>
Is something by which to soar<br>
Or a way to plant this seed<br>
<br>
A smile, pure and simple<br>
One of love or of happiness shared<br>
Just a showing of some teeth and a dimple<br>
Of a willingness to be bared<br>
<br>
So understand this as best you might<br>
For when you see a stranger there<br>
Give them a smile upon their sight<br>
And maybe ask them how they fare<br>
<br>
<br>
Simply put, be nice to people. Offer a smile to someone, regardless of whether you know them or not. Maybe offer them sow if you can or heals or buffs or what have you. You don't have to, but it makes quite the impression when done to them unexpectedly. I realize alot of you do...but some don't because it never occurs to them. Be safe, my friends...be well...<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
